/02/23/tca-ill-see-you-in-hell/',0,'post','',0),(149,1,'2007-02-26 14:14:42','2007-02-26 14:14:42','It\'s as if <a href=\"http://homepage.mac.com/steve/Resume.html\" target=\"_blank\">Steve</a> wanted to teach me a lesson. \"Never EVER buy a new Apple Product on day one\" Now I don\'t know why he would want to do that, but I certainly learned my lesson.\nWhy? Because!\nMy MBP is in for repair. Again. This time I think I fried the RAM. Now I\'m waiting for a call from the <a href=\"http://www.apple.com/uk/retail/westquay/week/20070225.html\" target=\"_blank\">Apple Store</a> to let me know that I can pick my machine up again. And I need the little fucker, because a lot of work is on there. And having weekly backups on Sundays is worth shit when your computer dies on you on Saturdays.\nEnough of that, it\'s time to stare at my phone again. RING!','Fracked...again','','publish','closed','open','','frackedagain','','','2007-02-26 14:14:42','2007-02-26 14:14:42','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/02/26/frackedagain/',0,'post','',0),(150,1,'2007-02-26 14:35:10','2007-02-26 14:35:10','<a href=\"http://googlemac.blogspot.com/2007/02/visit-to-apple.html\" target=\"_blank\">Work at Google (free food!) and visit Apple (Apple!).</a>','My new masterplan!','','publish','open','open','','my-new-masterplan','','','2007-02-26 14:35:10','2007-02-26 14:35:10','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/02/26/my-new-masterplan/',0,'post','',0),(151,1,'2007-02-26 19:22:45','2007-02-26 19:22:45','So, now I\'m sitting here with lots of stuff to do and virtually no way to do it.\nSure, I could download the zipped backups from my <a href=\"http://www.mac.com/\" target=\"blank\">iDisk</a>, but then I\'d have to repeat work I have already completed but just not backed up. And I still have high hopes that I\'ll get my <a href=\"http://www.apple-history.com/?page=gallery&amp;model=mbp&amp;performa=off&amp;sort=date&amp;order=ASC\" target=\"blank\">MacBook Pro</a> back with all my data intact.\nI wish that I had saved my finance table with <a href=\"http://docs.google.com/\" target=\"blank\">Google Spreadsheets</a>, so that I could at least fool around a bit with my projections. Because somehow I need to find a way to set aside the money for a second <a href=\"http://www.smartdisk.com/eWeb/smartdiskus/www/staticpages/crossfiredeskhdd.asp\" target=\"blank\">FireWire harddrive</a>. And a pair of nike+ shoes. The HDD has a slightly higher priority though.\nAlso, watch the <a href=\"http://www.themerlinshow.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Merlin Show</a>!','Helplessnessyness','','publish','open','open','','helplessnessyness','','','2007-02-26 19:22:45','2007-02-26 19:22:45','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/02/26/helplessnessyness/',0,'post','',0),(152,1,'2007-02-27 20:35:00','2007-02-27 20:35:00','Somehow I think there\'s an aura of disgust-inducing Digustinducium surrounding the Power Macs in the room I spend most of my MBP-free days in. Every couple of minutes people rush in. They look around with a hint of angst in their eyes. They see the logo and suddenly someone exclaims with a mixture of \"look at me, I\'m smarter than you!\"-pride and \"That dude just ate a bucket full of dog poo!\"-digust \"Oh...it\'s Apple MAAAAACS!\". Which makes them storm out as if Lucifer himself were coming after them.\nWhy? Hell, I don\'t know. But if it doesn\'t have a Start-Button, it can\'t be good.\nPeople are stupid.','Sitting with the Power Macs','','publish','open','open','','sitting-with-the-power-macs','','','2007-02-27 20:35:00','2007-02-27 20:35:00','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/02/27/sitting-with-the-power-macs/',0,'post','',0),(153,1,'2007-02-28 12:32:28','2007-02-28 12:32:28','Okay, I admit right away, it\'s all my fault. Yesterday was the first time that I actually witnessed the end of a pzizz-track. Might have had something to do with the cup of coffee I had had just a few hours before going to bed. Might have had something to do with the attempt to got to bed early.\nI have never felt as awake as I did at around midnight. But at least I felt quite refreshed this morning.\nSleep is weird.','Sleep. No sleep. Sleep. No sleep.','','publish','open','open','','sleep-no-sleep-sleep-no-sleep','','','2007-02-28 12:32:28','2007-02-28 12:32:28','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/02/28/sleep-no-sleep-sleep-no-sleep/',0,'post','',0),(154,1,'2007-03-02 17:31:56','2007-03-02 17:31:56','Finally, I got my MacBook back. Apparently they tried to call me a couple of times. Well, I didn\'t get any calls and there was no display of missed calls, but who cares.\nI\'ve got a lot to catch up with.','Back among the digital','','publish','open','open','','back-among-the-digital','','','2007-03-02 17:31:56','2007-03-02 17:31:56','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/03/02/back-among-the-digital/',0,'post','',0),(156,1,'2007-03-03 21:32:47','2007-03-03 21:32:47','<object width=\"425\" height=\"350\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/sHEMYkCN26A\"></param><param name=\"wmode\" value=\"transparent\"></param><embed src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/sHEMYkCN26A\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" wmode=\"transparent\" width=\"425\" height=\"350\"></embed></object>\n\n<a href=\'http://s207122144.online.de/wp-content/uploads/20070304.mov\' title=\'1 (04-03-2007)\'>1 (04-03-2007)</a>','The loneliest number','','publish','open','open','','the-loneliest-number','','','2007-03-03 21:32:47','2007-03-03 21:32:47','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/03/03/the-loneliest-number/',0,'post','',0),(157,1,'2007-03-04 15:34:57','2007-03-04 15:34:57','Never bring money into the Apple Store! Never!\nFinally I can begin my long awaited \"move all my media to the new HDD, format the old HDD, move the media back, do a complete backup of everything\"-operation. That is okay.\nBut you can\'t just go in there and buy 120 gigs of space, no. Now I also own speakers for my iPod. Well, no more music purchases until graduation.','Excess','','publish','closed','open','','excess','','','2007-03-04 15:34:57','2007-03-04 15:34:57','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/03/04/excess/',0,'post','',0),(158,1,'2007-03-08 23:07:28','2007-03-08 23:07:28','Felt rather crappy today. It began with Ze saying that he\'ll miss us. Made me sad.\nWell, then I went on to get some hooks on my to-do-list for today. Did some DCiJ, some Project 2, some e-Business.\nBut I just can\'t get a feeling for e-Business. I\'ve written almost 800 words that all circle around how cool corporate blogging is, but they don\'t actually say anything. Terribly frustrating. But at this point I really need to just push out the content and get all sections filled. At a later point in time I can still get back and punch some sense into the bastard.\nAh well, time to pzizz.','Maybe tomorrow will be a better day','','publish','open','open','','maybe-tomorrow-will-be-a-better-day','','','2007-03-08 23:07:28','2007-03-08 23:07:28','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/03/maybe-tomorrow-will-be-a-better-day/',0,'post','',0),(159,1,'2007-03-09 22:26:34','2007-03-09 22:26:34','I wonder who it is at ASDA that hates people.\nI bought cereal and milk earlier today. You know, to brighten up my morning and stuff.\nWell, apparently ASDA have exchanged their old white bags for transparent bags. Which is really nice, because now anyone can see what you just bought. And if you\'re really lucky, these people even feel inclined to prove their mad reading skillz. Want to know how many times I heard \"Coco Pops..huh huh\" within my ten-minute-walk? Just guess, you wouldn\'t be too far off.','Look at me, I can read!','','publish','open','open','','look-at-me-i-can-read','','','2007-03-09 22:26:34','2007-03-09 22:26:34','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/03/look-at-me-i-can-read/',0,'post','',0),(160,1,'2007-03-10 19:29:03','2007-03-10 19:29:03','Okay, I\'m giving <a href=\"http://quicksilver.blacktree.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Quicksilver</a> another chance. Must be the fourth or fifth try.\nI must admit, I\'m not exactly the most patient user. If I don\'t benefit from a program immediately, it can\'t be any good. At all. And so far Quicksilver never jumped at me and said \"Hey, this is why you should be using me!\". All I ever heard was other people saying how great Quicksilver is and that everybody should use it.\nSo far I got along pretty well with my combination of Spotlight and Overflow. But I have to say, at least Quicksilver is a lot faster at bringing up the files I want to use right now.\nAnyway, I\'ll just give it another  try.\n\n<em>Addendum:</em>\nI\'ve used Quicksilver since yesterday morning, almost non-stop. I have to say, I love it. I use the Flashlight interface, which formats Quicksilver to be a Spotlight-like field on the left side of the menu-bar. I\'ve used Spotlight maybe two times in the last days, Quicksilver having completely become my application launcher. Hell, I don\'t even use Overflow anymore.\nWhat I have come to love most about Quicksilver is the web-search. I call Quicksilver, press \"G\", tab twice and I can do a Google-search. On my desktop. Automatically calls Firefox and everything.\nI love Quicksilver.\n<span style=\"font-size: 0.7em\">(Though it could be a bit more stable.)</span>','Hey, I don\'t hate you. Yet.','','publish','closed','open','','hey-i-dont-hate-you-yet','','','2007-03-10 19:29:03','2007-03-10 19:29:03','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/03/hey-i-dont-hate-you-yet/',0,'post','',0),(161,1,'2007-03-11 09:46:18','2007-03-11 09:46:18','What the hell is up with my brain?\nMost of last night it spent showing me timetables. It then added new appointments to the table. And filled them with random words. Just to directly jump to people playing rugby in a medieval city, which led to the lamest possible Heroes-showdown, involving a handshake.\nBrain, you suck!','Then he went completely mental!','','publish','open','open','','then-he-went-completely-mental','','','2007-03-11 09:46:18','2007-03-11 09:46:18','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/03/then-he-went-completely-mental/',0,'post','',0),(162,1,'2007-03-12 11:10:43','2007-03-12 11:10:43','Oh joy, yesterday I discovered that all of us totally forgot that we not only have to pull 1500 words each out of our asses, we also have to hold presentations.\nWhen?\nNext week.\nCrap?\nHell yeah!\nI have my text ready. At least the first draft. But I\'d have no problem talking about my ideas and findings. Frederik will have his text ready this week, because he leaves the country on Friday.\nHuh?\nYes, next week we\'ll be three people. Great! And I haven\'t even seen anyone else\'s progress.\nI want to be dead.','Panic 2.0','','publish','closed','open','','panic-20','','','2007-03-12 11:10:43','2007-03-12 11:10:43','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/03/panic-20/',0,'post','',0),(163,1,'2007-03-13 11:46:02','2007-03-13 11:46:02','Finally, I have stopped the development of additional features for my final year project. From now on I can spend my time streamlining the code, fixing nasty bugs and writing extensive documentation.\nOh, and working on the four other projects I have on my list at the moment. Super!','Ice Age','','publish','open','open','','ice-age','','','2007-03-13 11:46:02','2007-03-13 11:46:02','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/03/ice-age/',0,'post','',0),(164,1,'2007-03-14 20:07:43','2007-03-14 20:07:43','Since I have started using Quicksilver I\'ve also fallen in love with Applescript.\nI\'ve been using PathFinder for a while now, having it set as my default file manager. It was just problematic that some programs would call the Finder and then there was no way to get rid of it.\nNow I have a nice little Applescript. I press ctrl-space, q, return. The Finder crawls back into its cave. (No, I\'m not a fan of triggers.)\nSame thing goes for emptying PathFinder\'s trash.\nToday for a few minutes I actually thought about building the presentation on monday as a script that uses Quicksilver\'s â€œLarge Typeâ€ function. I chose not to. Anyway.\nApplescript, you\'re awesome.','I\'m in love with a text file, shoot me!','','publish','open','open','','im-in-love-with-a-text-file-shoot-me','','','2007-03-14 20:07:43','2007-03-14 20:07:43','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/03/im-in-love-with-a-text-file-shoot-me/',0,'post','',0),(165,1,'2007-03-16 08:15:45','2007-03-16 08:15:45','Since my mom told me she had sent me a package for my birthday I went downstairs today to check if my name had already appeared on the magical â€œyou\'ve got mail!â€-board. It wasn\'t there. The girl in the office asked me if my name was â€œTshishikuâ€ or something, which is really close enough.\nSo yes, I had in fact three letters and a postcard. One of these letters was from the accommodation office, dated early February. It said that they weren\'t able to withdraw the second payment for my room from my account because the account does not exist.\nFirst of all I do have to admit that I should have checked my mail earlier even though my name had not been on the board for months.\nBut what\'s this about my account not existing? Where do I get that money from I live off? Where did I get the Â£1200 from that I carried through town today?\nAnyway, the money has been paid now and I\'ll just pay the next installment cash right away to save all of us a lot of trouble.','Not one of the greatest moments in time','','publish','open','open','','not-one-of-the-greatest-moments-in-time','','','2007-03-16 08:15:45','2007-03-16 08:15:45','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/03/not-one-of-the-greatest-moments-in-time/',0,'post','',0),(166,1,'2007-03-16 10:39:15','2007-03-16 10:39:15','<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Darkwing_Duck#.22Let.27s_get_dangerous.22_in_other_languages\">Get away from the propeller!</a>','The WTF Express','','publish','open','open','','the-wtf-express','','','2007-03-16 10:39:15','2007-03-16 10:39:15','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/03/the-wtf-express/',0,'post','',0),(167,1,'2007-03-16 23:47:57','2007-03-16 23:47:57','No updates until Monday. I need to get this presentation-thing out of the way first.\nJust so that you know, if I ever were to kill a man, it might very well happen within the next nine days. You heard it here first!','Other things','','publish','open','open','','other-things','','','2007-03-16 23:47:57','2007-03-16 23:47:57','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/03/other-things/',0,'post','',0),(168,1,'2007-03-18 13:21:29','2007-03-18 13:21:29','I have mentioned the presentation-situation before. Here\'s just a little update on how we\'re doing.\nFrederik is gone. I have sort of built a couple of slides to be able to force the introduction, his part, my part and the conclusion into five minutes.\nOn Monday I had told the guys that I needed their notes and the content for their slides on Friday. And I actually got something from Bijan. Obviously I got nothing from Sebastian.\nYesterday we went to uni to check out the equipment in the room and do a couple of rehearsals. The room was locked. Sebastian showed up with a piece of paper with a couple of notes on it. His content at that point was basically â€œThere are pictures on the site, which is good...and lock-in!â€. Dude has some balls, I have to give him that.\nSo today we have another rehearsal, hopefully in the room we\'ll be in on Monday. A couple of minutes ago I got an IM from Bijan, telling me that he has too much of a hangover to come today. Which means that he will stand there on Monday without ever having rehearsed the presentation with us. Told you, I will kill people!\nLuckily we get individual marks for the presentation.','The Presentation Chronicles: Sunday','','publish','open','open','','the-presentation-chronicles-sunday','','','2007-03-18 13:21:29','2007-03-18 13:21:29','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/03/the-presentation-chronicles-sunday/',0,'post','',0),(169,1,'2007-03-19 19:53:40','2007-03-19 19:53:40','Monday, 12:30. Got up at 6:30 to check the equipment in the presentation room. Everything seems to work fine. Hopefully it will still work when we get there later. I\'m dying a thousand deaths inside. Next it\'s the last rehearsal. Here we go!\n\nBijan did not appear to the rehearsal. He showed up a couple of minutes before the presentation. At that point I didn\'t even care anymore. So we just did the whole thing and earned 57 pathetic percent. Well, that\'s not exactly bad, it\'s a 2.2 getting close to a 2.1. But still, 57 is really nothing to be proud of.','Presentations, what better to ruin a birthday with!','','publish','open','open','','presentations-what-better-to-ruin-a-birthday-with','','','2007-03-19 19:53:40','2007-03-19 19:53:40','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/03/presentations-what-better-to-ruin-a-birthday-with/',0,'post','',0),(170,1,'2007-03-20 20:32:56','2007-03-20 20:32:56','<ol>\n<li>Defined some Quicksilver triggers. I have my to-do-list now at Ctrl-Cmd-T and I can empty my trash with Ctrl-Cmd-E. From anywhere. Sweet.</li>\n<li>Read a lot of that damn Moby Dick. That book will never end.</li>\n<li>Did a lot of Java, some proof-reading and later on I need to do some mind-mapping.</li>\n<li>Actually worked on something creative for a change. As soon as the concept has become more transparent to me I will post a little preview.</li>\n</ol>\nThat\'s it for today, back to work.','What I did today','','publish','open','open','','what-i-did-today','','','2007-03-20 20:32:56','2007-03-20 20:32:56','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/03/what-i-did-today/',0,'post','',0),(171,1,'2007-03-21 22:34:57','2007-03-21 22:34:57','Big e-business crunch-day tomorrow. I wonder when I will actually get all those texts.\nI bet not before noon.\nWe\'ll see.','Tired','','publish','open','open','','tired','','','2007-03-21 22:34:57','2007-03-21 22:34:57','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/03/tired/',0,'post','',0),(172,1,'2007-03-22 20:48:35','2007-03-22 20:48:35','Wow, I just sat down to write an amazing post about how I finally rolled out the final version of the e-business paper. Turns out I can\'t write or even think anymore. Well, update will follow tomorrow.','Can\'t...even...write...','','publish','closed','open','','cantevenwrite','','','2007-03-22 20:48:35','2007-03-22 20:48:35','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/03/cantevenwrite/',0,'post','',0),(173,1,'2007-03-23 10:26:22','2007-03-23 10:26:22','Here\'s the promised update.<br />\nThe e-business-paper is done. Yesterday morning I had actually received the texts from Sebastian and Bijan. Funny story, their e-mails both had a ring to them, that the deadline of &ldquo;Wednesday, midnight!&rdquo; was sort of a surprise. It\'s not that you can forget a lot in two weeks, but I had reminded them a couple of times in the meantime.<br />\nWell, so I got all those texts, sadly not proof-read by someone who knows ze Englishs. So I spent about five hours re-writing Bijans text. I mean, not that his English is bad, but about one third of his text was directly copied from the paper our course is based on and from e-mails I had gotten from the companies we talked to. Copied, not quoted. Oh, and also his arguments were sometimes...let\'s say questionable.<br />\nHere\'s a sample (summarized): The OmniGroup sell boxed versions of their products through offline stores. Stores need websites! Omni should demand that their affiliates have websites! Therefore Omni should only collaborate with stores that ship within 24 hours via UPS or FedEx.<br />\nI guess that makes sense. Somehow. You know, I like those mini-donuts from ASDA. ASDA is a huge chain. Stores need to sell products. Therefore the donuts should be red! Or else!!!<br />\nBy the time I had produced 1500 new words (some of them entirely new! patent pending.) Frederik offered to proof-read Sebastian\'s text. I was glad, since I  had given up after reading Sebastian\'s first paragraph. So I could take about half an hour off, waiting for Frederik to get done. And done he got...get...done...gotten...Schumpeter! I\'m pretty sure the original text was even more of a train-wreck, but what I got back was still an insult to...everything. So, I wrote another 1500 words inspired by Sebastian\'s findings, such as &ldquo;3D-images are good because people can identify them with things they have held in their hand before, such as a lorry or a biro&rdquo;. Sweet.<br />\nOh, and <a href=&ldquo;http://marcoliverteschke.tumblr.com/post/293570&ldquo;>here\'s</a> a <a href=&ldquo;http://marcoliverteschke.tumblr.com/post/293570&ldquo;>link</a> to a simply beautiful <a href=&ldquo;http://marcoliverteschke.tumblr.com/post/293570&ldquo;>dialogue</a> Frederik and Sebastian had while Freddy was reading Sebastian\'s text. You know, just to push my <a href=&rdquo;http://marcoliverteschke.tumblr.com&rdquo;>tumblelog</a> a bit.<br />\nAfter 11 hours I had pulled 3000 words of text for Bijan and Sebastian out of my ass, as well as a few lines for introduction and conclusion.<br />\nHand-in in three hours. Life is beautiful.<br />','E-Business: Almost there','','publish','open','open','','e-business-almost-there','','','2007-03-23 10:26:22','2007-03-23 10:26:22','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/03/e-business-almost-there/',0,'post','',0),(174,1,'2007-03-24 15:28:15','2007-03-24 15:28:15','Yeees, I know, I shouldn\'t actually be writing this, since today is &ldquo;Shutdown Day&rdquo;. I actually quite liked the idea to spend a whole day without the computer.<br />\nSadly I\'ve had more than enough shutdown days in the last year, so I think I don\'t need to prove anything to a site that allows me to upload pictures of me not using a computer.<br />\nSo, this is day two of my new &ldquo;5 day crunch&rdquo;-project. I\'m trying to complete all of my projects in five days each. Meaning that I have roughly three days left to complete WDfI assignment 4. Then I\'ll take a day off and then I\'ll start the next project. I\'ll see how it goes. I must say, I\'ve already come quite far with WDfI, so it might actually work.<br />\nI\'m just lacking a bit of motivation at the moment.','Shutdown Day','','publish','open','open','','shutdown-day','','','2007-03-24 15:28:15','2007-03-24 15:28:15','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/03/shutdown-day/',0,'post','',0),(175,1,'2007-03-24 20:52:27','2007-03-24 20:52:27','I haven\'t done anything musical in quite some time. So I tried pushing myself to do something for weeks, without success. I\'m a really visual person, so I need to see something before my eyes to get a feeling for it. I just couldn\'t find the right inspiration.\nFor the past two months or so I struggled with Moby Dick. It\'s not that it is a bad book or anything, but I always need a long time to get a feeling for any book. By the time I get close to the end I usually regret that there are only so few pages left. Same with Moby Dick. Plus now I had an idea.\nThe last three chapters, the final struggle with the white whale, turned into sound. So I fired up my GarageBand and started my dark, amateurish work. Today I got to a point with the first three minutes, where I said â€œOkay, I need a break.â€œ!\nHere are the first three minutes, I hope there are six more to come soon. It is still work in progress. And you can clearly hear where the Apple Loops stop and my own work begins. Additionally, I found out that I have no feeling for how to do good transitions.\nWhatever, here you go:\n[audio:http://www.damot.org/media/Musik/GWW.mp3]','Thar he blows. Let\'s listen.','','publish','open','open','','thar-he-blows-lets-listen','','','2007-03-24 20:52:27','2007-03-24 20:52:27','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/03/thar-he-blows-lets-listen/',0,'post','',0),(176,1,'2007-03-27 18:42:24','2007-03-27 18:42:24','Today was London-day. The weather was great. The Weather Widget lied to me, so I brought my coat and my umbrella and carried that shit around all day.\nI also left in kind of a hurry and forgot my camera. So no photos of a sunny London.\nOn the train to London we passed a town were everyone seemed to have a giant trampoline in their garden. Seems to be sort of en vogue to have one these days. I wonder if I could fit one into my room.\nLuckily I looked at my booking information again yesterday and saw, that I actually booked my trip to London by train. Would have been rather embarrassing if I had waited for the bus all day.\nWhile walking on a bridge across the Thames I noticed that London smells like armpits and sugar. Weird combination. But surprisingly enticing.\nI also walked past something that was either a woman with a mustache that would make Prussian generals cry in envy or just a dude wearing a skirt. I wonder what would be more unusual these days.\nOh, and the service at Niketown sucks.\nâ€œHi, I\'m looking for a Nike+ compatible running shoe.â€\nâ€œWhat kind of running?â€\nâ€œNothing serious. Just a few rounds through the park every day.â€\nâ€œWell, these are our running shoes. This is a running shoe. This is a running shoe, too. These cost more than those. But they\'re all running shoes.â€\nWell thank you.\nThen he ran off to join one of his colleagues in taking care of a female customer. Sure, I can understand his motives, but honestly, the shoes in the Nike+ section on the â€œRunningâ€ rack are actually running shoes? I can fucking read, but you\'re supposed to know which ones I need for which type of running. He then had a strange machine fetch me a pair in my size and after I had been ignored for another twenty minutes while I tried the shoes he was actually nice enough to mention all the other gear I should buy. Gaaah.','London-day...again','','publish','open','open','','london-dayagain','','','2007-03-27 18:42:24','2007-03-27 18:42:24','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/03/london-dayagain/',0,'post','',0),(177,1,'2007-03-29 20:54:29','2007-03-29 20:54:29','Started the implementation of the DCiJ project today. Had lots of fun trying to configure the Tomcat server. It really seems to hate me.\nThen it suddenly did not want to launch anymore, because an instance of it was still running. I tried to kill it and Windows froze. Reboot. Bluescreen. Reboot. Bluescreen. Repair from the installation disk. Bluescreen. Backed up files from the Boot Camp partition. Reinstalled. â€œCould not find file XYZFUCKYOU.dllâ€ Removed the partition. Installed Windows in Parallels. Spent an hour fighting with the network configuration. Finally started installing 80 updates. Still waiting.\nWell, at least I got the persistence layer of the app running today. I just hope the project will be easy to reintegrate tomorrow.','Oh Windows, you dick!','','publish','open','open','','oh-windows-you-dick','','','2007-03-29 20:54:29','2007-03-29 20:54:29','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/03/oh-windows-you-dick/',0,'post','',0),(178,1,'2007-04-01 16:39:12','2007-04-01 16:39:12','I\'m getting lazy, not just when it comes to writing on the blog. I try to get at least 5 items on my to do list done each day now. Not that successfully.\nThe Java-project is moving slowly. Still can\'t find any motivation. I hope to get the basic functionality finished tomorrow. Then there\'ll only be â€œmaking it work just rightâ€ and â€œmaking it look prettyâ€ left to do. Aside from writing the documentation, of course.\nThe big project is also coming along. I started cleaning up the code yesterday and since then the quality has significantly gone downhill. Well, at least I won\'t get bored anytime soon. Lots of documentation waiting to be written here as well.\nNeed to start packing tomorrow.','What am I doing? Nothing!','','publish','open','open','','what-am-i-doing-nothing','','','2007-04-01 16:39:12','2007-04-01 16:39:12','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/04/what-am-i-doing-nothing/',0,'post','',0),(179,1,'2007-04-01 23:59:59','2007-04-01 23:59:59','<ul class=\"aktt_tweet_digest\">\n	<li>Good episode. Rare these days. Now out for a run. <a href=\"http://twitter.com/marcoliver/statuses/17182001\">#</a></li>\n	<li>Uuuh, new Beatles on iTunes rumors emerging. Hope it\'s not April 1st fracking with us. <a href=\"http://twitter.com/marcoliver/statuses/17200901\">#</a></li>\n	<li>Spamming friends\' guestbooks. <a href=\"http://twitter.com/marcoliver/statuses/17230101\">#</a></li>\n	<li>Getting tired. Again. Always when it gets dark outside. What\'s up with that? <a href=\"http://twitter.com/marcoliver/statuses/17273651\">#</a></li>\n</ul>','Twitter Updates for 2007-04-01','','publish','open','open','','twitter-updates-for-2007-04-01','','','2007-04-01 23:59:59','2007-04-01 23:59:59','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/04/twitter-updates-for-2007-04-01/',0,'post','',0),(180,1,'2007-04-02 16:50:31','2007-04-02 16:50:31','Something weird just happened. I just realized that for a week or so all my clocks had been one hour ahead of reality. That might be why I always felt so tired when I woke up in the morning. It actually explains an awful lot of things including why most stores in town were just opening up when I went there around 10, which was actually 9.','Time traveller','','publish','open','open','','time-traveller','','','2007-04-02 16:50:31','2007-04-02 16:50:31','',0,'http://www.damot.org/2007/04/time-traveller/',0,'post','',0),(181,1,'2007-04-02 23:59:59','2007-04-02 23:59:59','<ul>\n	<li>Awake. Once again. Lots of stuff to do today. Would like more sleep though. <a href=\"http://twitter.com/marcoliver/statuses/17450921\">#</a></li>\n	<li>Errand-running. Let\'s go! <a href=\"http://twitter.com/marcoliver/statuses/17514371\">#</a></li>\n	<li>Back already. That was quick. More time to get my work done. <a href=\"http://twitter.com/marcoliver/statuses/17531591\">#</a></li>\n	<li>Waiting for my laundry to get done. <a href=\"http://twitter.com/marcoliver/statuses/17541361\">#</a></li>\n	<li>Dreamed about PuzzleQuest last night. Creepy. <a href=\"http://twitter.com/marcoliver/statuses/17546491\">#</a></li>\n	<li>What the hell? All my clocks were wrong. I\'ve been living one hour ahead of everybody else for a week or so. <a href=\"http://twitter.com/marcoliver/statuses/17596541\">#</a></li>\n	<li>Now it gets interesting. <a href=\"http://twitter.com/marcoliver/statuses/17613051\">#</a></li>\n	<li>Paul Thurrott had the dumbest comment on the EMI announcement yet. Way to go <a href=\"http://twitter.com/marcoliver/statuses/17628351\">#</a></li>\n	<li>On an intense bug-hunt in my project-code. <a href=\"http://twitter.com/marcoliver/statuses/17760381\">#</a></li>\n	<li>Cleared my to do list for today. <a href=\"http://twitter.com/marcoliver/statuses/17781691\">#</a></li>\n	<li>Should I have another pizza? My brain says \"yes\", my stomach says \"no\". <a href=\"http://twitter.com/marcoliver/statuses/17784681\">#</a></li>\n	<li>@nick: Of course I mean an entire pizza. Anything else is for weenies. <a href=\"http://twitter.com/marcoliver/statuses/17787541\">#</a></li>\n	<li>@stomach: I am your master, you shall suffer from my imaginary hunger! <a href=\"http://twitter.com/marcoliver/statuses/17787911\">#</a></li>\n	<li>It\'s pineapple anyway, so at least it\'s...\"light\". <a href=\"http://twitter.com/marcoliver/statuses/17788711\">#</a></li>\n	<li>@nick: Well, the pizza-duo will be my lunch and dinner in one. Not everybody has such a firm grip on time to have lunch at lunchtime. <a href=\"http://twitter.com/marcoliver/statuses/17791641\">#</a></li>\n	<li>Watching PvP The Series episode 3. Best episode ever! So far. <a href=\"http://twitter.com/marcoliver/statuses/17801521\">#</a></li>\n	<li>@davor: No idea. I\'ve never had premiere. <a href=\"http://twitter.com/marcoliver/statuses/17811651\">#</a></li>\n	<li>Creating a copy of the project database. <a href=\"http://twitter.com/marcoliver/statuses/17839941\">#</a></li>\n	<li>At 800 entries the system completely caves in. That\'ll make for an interesting chapter in the documentation. <a href=\"http://twitter.com/marcoliver/statuses/17868471\">#</a></li>\n	<li>Oh great, just before I leave my DSL line the Joost people throw out new invites. Not even worth begging. <a href=\"http://twitter.com/marcoliver